tflowtools

Class TrainableNetwork

  • java.lang.Object
    • tflowtools.TrainableNetwork

  • public class TrainableNetwork
extends Object
    A wrapper for creating, training, and evaluating TensorFlow models. Normally the syntax is a pain in Java, so this just keeps me from having to remember all of it.
    Author:
    matt

    • Method Detail

      • trainingStep

        public float trainingStep(float[][] inputs,
                          float[][] desiredOutputs,
                          int steps)
        Run training on a set of data.
        Parameters:
        inputs - One or more sets of inputs. First dimension is the example number. Second dimension is the size of each example.
        desiredOutputs - Outputs which we want inputs to produce.
        steps - Number of training steps (some form of gradient descent) to use on this set of inputs.
        Returns:
        The loss of the last step performed (smaller is better).

      • saveCheckpoint

        public void saveCheckpoint(String checkpointName)
        Save training progress (i.e. weights and biases) to specific checkpoint file. Will still be saved to the checkpoint directory. Do not include file extension.

      • loadCheckpoint

        public void loadCheckpoint(String checkpointName)
        Load a checkpoint file. Must match the graph loaded. Name does not need to include path or file extension.
        Parameters:
        checkpointName - Name of the checkpoint to load.

      • evaluateInput

        public float[][] evaluateInput(float[][] inputs)
        Evaluate one or more inputs to the net. Does not perform any training.
        Parameters:
        inputs - One or more inputs to feed in. For a single example, the first dimension should be 1.
        Returns:
        The evaluated values of the inputs.

      • printGraphOperations

        public void printGraphOperations()
        Print all operations in the graph for debugging.

      • getNumberOfOperationOutputs

        public int getNumberOfOperationOutputs(String operationName)
        Get the number of outputs from a specified operation. This is NOT the same as the dimension of the output. In most cases, the number of outputs will be 1.
        Parameters:
        operationName - Name of the operation to check on.
        Returns:
        Number of outputs returned by that operation.

      • getShapeOfOperationOutput

        public int[] getShapeOfOperationOutput(String operationName,
                                       int outputIdx)
        Get the dimensions of an output of an operation. Note that any -1 dimension is one of unknown size (e.g. number of samples being fed in).
        Parameters:
        operationName - Name of the operation to examine.
        outputIdx - Index of the output of the operation to examine (usually 0). Not the same as shape!
        Returns:
        An array of sizes of the dimensions of the output.

      • getLayerSizes

        public int[] getLayerSizes()
        Get the sizes of the fully-connected layers in the net. These should include inputs and outputs.
        Returns:
        Array of the sizes of the inputs/outputs of the fully-connected layers of the net.

      • getGraphDefinitionFile

        public File getGraphDefinitionFile()
        Get the .pb file which defines the network. Does not include weights.
        Returns:
        The tensorflow network definition file.

      • makeNewNetwork

        public static TrainableNetwork makeNewNetwork(String graphName,
                                              List<Integer> layerSizes,
                                              List<String> additionalArgs)
                                       throws FileNotFoundException
        Create a new fully-connected neural network structure. This calls a python script to make the net.
        Parameters:
        graphName - Name of the graph file (without path or file extension).
        layerSizes - List of layer sizes. Make sure that the first and last layers match the inputs and desired output sizes.
        additionalArgs - Additional inputs defined by the python script. Make sure that the list is separated out by each word in the command line.
        Returns:
        A new TrainableNetwork based on the specifications.
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException
